                             THE TECHNICAL STUFF

SANTA runs on any BBS capable of generating a standard DorinfoX.Def or
Door.Sys drop file. In fact, Rich runs a WildCat! board, while Rey runs
PCBoard. Features of SANTA include DOS shelling, various timer functions
(caller's time left, input-timer whenever remote input is expected, SysOp
hot-keys to increase or decrease caller's time), carrier detection, FOSSIL
support, non-standard IRQ support, CTS checking and more. You can check the
caller's stats while the door is in operation. SANTA writes a log in case you
weren't around when Santa had that little chat with a caller as well as a
separate file which logs errors, perish the thought.

                    ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

Here's what's required to implement SANTA on your board:

Make a separate directory where you will run SANTA. Unzip all the files in
the archive into this directory. Next, you must modify Santa.Cfg to reflect
the correct information for your board (see below).

