                    ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

Optional command-line switches:

FOSSIL  - Enable FOSSIL support. If you do not use a FOSSIL driver (such as
          X00 or BNU) do not use this switch.

FULL    - Force SANTA into full-screen mode regardless of the user's
          graphics settings.  Rey prefers this because it properly displays
          a Santa graphic and the longer Santa responses, but Split Screen
          is the more 'professional' looking display.  Suit yourself.

IRQ=x   - Change the default IRQ to "x".

LOCAL   - Run SANTA in local mode, from the command line.

SPLIT   - Force SANTA into split-screen mode.

TIME=x  - Limits the caller to x% of his time-left in the door.

                    ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

SANTA is run with the following syntax: SANTA  (pretty tough, huh?)

EXAMPLE DoorX.Bat:

@Echo Off
Echo       * Paged Santa >> C:\Wc30\Activity.001
Cd \Doors\Santa
SANTA Fossil Time=80

For a quick demonstration, SANTA can be run from the command line by
typing: SANTA Local

                    ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

This documentation is not intended to be a tutorial on door setup. If you've
never set up a door before, please refer to your BBS documentation.

WILDCAT! SYSOPS: The example batch file will work only if you have WildCat!
set to SHELL to doors (refer to your in the WildCat! manual - it's on page
221 in Rich's).

PCBOARD SYSOPS: Toggle USER.SYS N and DOOR.SYS Y   There are no heavy mem
requirements so if you don't have to shell out for other Doors you shouldn't
for this one.  You (not the caller) may see a status line reporting that every
caller is 92 years old.  Rey thinks he knows why and expects that on January
1st they will all have a birthday. <g>

