                          The Freeware Hall of Fame


The HOF does everything we can to circulate good, tested Freeware to any BBS
that wants it, and we operate a free BBS offering unlimited downloads in the
first or any call.

The FHOF exists to give away files to sysops and callers. We provide sysops
with a package of 136 selected Freeware programs you can add to your BBS
download directory structure. The file descriptions come formatted for
PCBoard, RemoteAccess, QuickBBS, SuperBBS and Majic. When that 4.5 meg packet
is being downloaded from us the clock is off. Sysops have unlimited time to
get it, whether at 14400 baud or 1200.

Currently we count approximately 70 Bulletin Boards in North America and
Europe that make this DIR available to callers but they're just the ones we
know of, sysops who picked it up from us. We have no way of keeping up with
secondary transfers from one BBS to another.

We also publish and frequently update a sorted Guide to tested Freeware which
is found on Bulletin Boards all over the world. That file is called HOFmmyy.
The most recent is HOF1192, 39-pages when printed. The Guide is sorted 3 ways:
by author, program name, and type.

The third function of the Hall of Fame is to encourage, promote, design and
test Freeware (Santa is an example), working with programmers to produce more
Free programs. We alpha and beta test them and when the programs are ready we
distribute them to a baseline network of bulletin boards. From there callers
spread them all over the world.

